      'recoup.title':'Recoupment & advances','recoup.sub':'Advances and recoupable costs offset against earned royalties (lifetime balance).',
      'recoup.artist':'Artist','recoup.note':'Note','recoup.add':'+ Add',
      'recoup.advance':'Advance','recoup.cost':'Recoupable cost',
      'recoup.recoupable':'Recoupable','recoup.royalties':'Royalties (lifetime)','recoup.recouped':'Recouped',
      'recoup.unrecouped':'Unrecouped','recoup.payable':'Payable',
      'recoup.empty':'No advances or costs recorded.','recoup.need':'Enter artist and amount',
      'info.recoup':`<h4>What Recoupment is for</h4>
          <p>When you advance money to an artist (an <b>advance</b>) or cover <b>recoupable costs</b> on their behalf (studio, video, promo), those amounts must be <b>recovered from their royalties</b> before you pay them the rest.</p>
          <p>Here you record advances and costs per artist. The app compares the <b>total recoupable</b> with the <b>earned royalties</b> (lifetime) and shows how much has already been <b>recouped</b>, how much is left (<b>unrecouped</b>) and how much, if any, is <b>payable</b> to the artist beyond recoupment.</p>
          <span class="ex">Example — €1,000 advance to Raho. Royalties earned so far: €700. → Recouped €700, <b>unrecouped</b> €300, payable €0. Once royalties pass €1,000, the difference becomes "payable".</span>`,
      'plan.big.desc':'All the power of Label Finance for a single label.','pf.big1':'1 label','pf.big2':'Everything in Starter','pf.big3':'🤖 <b>Dedicated AI</b> Assistant','pf.big4':'Customizable dashboard + widgets','pf.big5':'Excel export + your branded documents','pf.big6':'Priority support','plan.studio.desc':'For managing multiple labels: everything, up to 3 labels.','pf.studio1':'Everything in Big Label','pf.studio2':'Up to 3 labels','pf.studio3':'Multi-label management','pf.studio5':'Per-artist royalty statements','pf.studio6':'Priority support','plan.agency.desc':'For agencies and groups: unlimited labels and tailored features.','pf.agency1':'Everything in Company','pf.agency2':'Unlimited labels','pf.agency3':'Team access <em>(coming soon)</em>','pf.agency4':'Tailored features, on request','pf.agency5':'Dedicated onboarding','off.soon':'Coming soon',
      'off.pm':'/month',
      'info.planning':'<h4>What Planning is for</h4><p>Schedule your <b>releases</b> and <b>premieres</b> over time: use the status to tell a <b>simulation</b> (idea/planned) apart from an <b>actual</b> one (confirmed/released). View everything as a sortable <b>list</b> or as a <b>calendar</b> where you can add entries by clicking a day.</p>','info.events':'<h4>What the Events section is for</h4><p>Manage all the info about <b>showcases, radio events, live shows, festivals and club nights</b>: type, venue, city, date and time, with notes. Sortable <b>list</b> view or <b>calendar</b>.</p>','info.supports':'<h4>What the DJ Support section is for</h4><p>Keep track of <b>support</b>: which DJs play your tracks, in which <b>venues, cities and countries</b> around the world and when. A handy database for promotion and reporting.</p>','info.artists':'<h4>What the Artists directory is for</h4><p>Collect all your artists\' information here: stage name, legal name, email, phone, IBAN for payments, photo and a default split share. This data is reused to generate <b>contracts</b> and to remind you of <b>payments</b> in your tasks.</p>','info.contracts':'<h4>How contracts work</h4><p>You fill in the release and artist details, choose the split (by default <b>50% artist / 50% label</b>) and press <b>Generate contract</b>: you get the label\'s standard <b>Authorization to Release</b>, identical for everyone — only the split changes if you adjust it. From there you can <b>print it/save it as PDF</b>, <b>send it to the artist</b> for signing and archive the signed version.</p>','info.tasks':'<h4>What Tasks are for</h4><p>Keep track of things to do: pay an artist, send a contract, renew a distribution. Add a <b>due date</b> and the task will be highlighted when it\'s coming up or overdue. Tick the dot when it\'s done.</p>','info.merch':'<h4>What the Merch section is for</h4><p>Manage your merchandising (t-shirts, vinyl, CDs, posters…): for each item you set the <b>price</b>, <b>cost</b> and <b>stock</b>. When you sell, press <b>+ sale</b> and the system updates units sold, revenue, margin and inventory. At the top you\'ll find the totals and the best-selling item; you can also add the merch card to the dashboard.</p>',
      'confirm.del_label':'Delete label "{name}" and all its data? This cannot be undone.','confirm.load_demo':'Load demo data into this label?','confirm.wipe_all':'Erase ALL data (all labels) from this device? This cannot be undone.',
